# Architecture Rules

## Where things live
- `src/types/index.ts` — ALL domain types and enums. Single source of truth.
  Never define a type anywhere else. Never split into multiple files.
- `src/utils/` — pure functions only (no React, no DOM, no localStorage)
- `src/services/` — side effects: StorageService, CalculationEngine, testCases
- `src/context/AppContext.tsx` — all global state via useReducer
- `src/components/shared/` — cross-feature UI primitives
- `src/components/calibration/` — calibration wizard
- `src/components/intake/` — intake form sections
- `src/components/schedule/` — matrix, summary, drill-down, scope tab
- `src/views/` — top-level routed pages (orchestrate components, own section state)

## State rules
- Global state lives in AppContext only. Dispatch an action; never mutate directly.
- Local UI state (open/closed, active tab, editing index) stays in the component.
- Components never call localStorage directly — use StorageService.
- ScheduleOutput is never persisted. It is always recomputed from model + project.

## Actions available in AppContext
SET_ROLE | SET_MODEL | CLEAR_MODEL | SET_PROJECT | CLEAR_PROJECT |
SET_SCHEDULE | CLEAR_SCHEDULE | SET_SCOPE_DOC | MARK_MODEL_CLEAN | MARK_PROJECT_CLEAN

## One component per file. Named exports only.
